Patch Set 1:

Changes recommended by GTK+ maintainers from RHEL, see bug 573983 comment 13.

I ran Eclipse and did basic operations involving menus, there weren't problems:

1. From a Java editor, right-click to run a Java snippet.
2. From main menu, go to Window -> Preferences.
3. From Package Explorer, right-click on a Java source file with a main() method and run it from the context menu.

Using the snippet from bug 573983 comment 6, the leak also seems to be "gone". The biggest leak I see, involving menu creation is:

[16384 bytes leaked]
slab_allocator_alloc_chunk (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/glib/gslice.c:1330)
g_slice_alloc (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/glib/gslice.c:1014)
g_slice_alloc0 (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/glib/gslice.c:1051)
g_type_create_instance (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gtype.c:1848)
g_object_new_internal (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gobject.c:1799)
g_object_new_with_properties (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gobject.c:1967)
g_object_new (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gobject.c:1639)
Java_org_eclipse_swt_internal_gtk3_GTK3_gtk_1menu_1new (??:?)
?? (??:0)

This leak no longer grows, it remains the same e.g. even with 500 repetitions. Without the fix, the biggest leak at 100 repetitions is:

[114688 bytes leaked]
slab_allocator_alloc_chunk (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/glib/gslice.c:1330)
g_slice_alloc (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/glib/gslice.c:1014)
g_slice_alloc0 (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/glib/gslice.c:1051)
g_type_create_instance (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gtype.c:1848)
g_object_new_internal (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gobject.c:1799)
g_object_new_with_properties (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gobject.c:1967)
g_object_new (/usr/src/debug/glib-2.56.1/gobject/gobject.c:1639)
Java_org_eclipse_swt_internal_gtk3_GTK3_gtk_1menu_1new (??:?)
?? (??:0)

So I assume the leak is fixed with the change, and I didn't find obvious problems from the fix.
